## Definitions

“Licensor” means R4V3N.
“Software” means the Fluent Signal Copier codebase and all associated files, including without limitation Python scripts, MQL5 Expert or Indicator files, TypeScript or React frontend, compiled artifacts, configuration, documentation, and any updates or patches provided by Licensor.
“User” means the individual or legal entity that downloads, installs, or uses the Software.
“Seat” means one named natural person authorized to use the Software.
“Device” means a single physical or virtual machine instance.
“MT5 Account” means one MetaTrader 5 trading account.
“Update” means any bug fix, patch, enhancement, or new version of the Software provided by Licensor.

1. Acceptance

By installing, copying, or using the Software, User accepts this License. If User does not agree, do not install or use the Software.

2. Grant of License

Subject to continuous compliance with this License, Licensor grants User a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable license to install and use the Software for personal or internal business purposes. Unless a separate written agreement says otherwise, the license is limited to:
a. up to one Seat;
b. one production MT5 Account and one demo MT5 Account;
c. use on up to two Devices used by that Seat, active on no more than two Devices in any rolling 24-hour window.
User may make a reasonable number of machine-generated copies solely for installation, backup, and archival purposes. All rights not expressly granted are reserved by Licensor.

3. Restrictions

User may not:
a. modify, adapt, translate, port, merge, or create derivative works of the Software;
b. remove or alter proprietary notices or technological measures;
c. publish, distribute, sublicense, sell, rent, lease, lend, host, provide as a managed service, or otherwise make the Software available to third parties, including “signal copier as a service”;
d. use the Software to operate trading for third parties except with Licensor’s prior written consent;
e. use outputs, heuristics, logs, or performance data to build, train, or fine-tune any model or competing product;
f. benchmark or publish comparative results without prior written consent.

4. Reverse Engineering

User shall not reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble the Software, or attempt to derive source code or underlying ideas of any compiled components, obfuscated assets, or build artifacts, except to the minimum extent permitted by mandatory law for interoperability and only after providing prior written notice to Licensor and giving Licensor a reasonable opportunity to provide the necessary information.

5. Output and Data Use

User may use trading results and logs for personal or internal business analysis. User may not extract, repackage, resell, or redistribute signals or processing pipelines derived primarily from the Software, nor use outputs to train any machine learning or statistical model.

6. Security, Trading, and Regulatory Disclaimer

The Software interacts with third-party platforms and networks, including Telegram and MetaTrader 5. Automated trading involves substantial risk and may result in financial loss. The Software provides no investment advice and offers no performance guarantees. User alone is responsible for configuration, risk limits, demo testing, broker compatibility, compliance with financial services rules, data protection, and third-party platform terms.

